Cloud Peak Energy Finance Corp.: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 27, 2017 12:02 PM ET
Oil, Gas and Consumable Fuels

Company Overview of Cloud Peak Energy Finance Corp.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Cloud Peak Energy Finance Corp. was incorporated in 2009 and is based in Gillette, Wyoming. Cloud Peak Energy Finance Corp. operates as a subsidiary of Cloud Peak Energy Resources LLC.


505 South Gillette AvenueP.O. Box 3009Gillette, WY 82716-3009United StatesFounded in 2009










Key Executives for Cloud Peak Energy Finance Corp.


Cloud Peak Energy Finance Corp. does not have any Key Executives recorded. 



Cloud Peak Energy Finance Corp. Key Developments

Cloud Peak Energy Resources and Cloud Peak Energy Finance Corp Announce Final Results of its Exchange Offers
Oct 13 16
Cloud Peak Energy Inc. announced the final results of the offers to exchange by its direct and indirect wholly-owned subsidiaries, Cloud Peak Energy Resources LLC and Cloud Peak Energy Finance Corp. of up to $400,000,000 aggregate principal amount of their outstanding 8.50% Senior Notes due 2019 and 6.375% Senior Notes due 2024, for new secured 12.00% second lien notes due 2021 to be issued by the issuers and, in some cases, cash consideration, upon the terms and conditions described in the issuers’ offer to exchange dated September 12, 2016. The Exchange Offers expired at 11:59 p.m., New York City time, on October 12, 2016. The Exchange Offers are expected to settle on October 17, 2016. For 8.50% Senior Notes due 2019, a principle amount of $237,906,000 with 79.30% and for 6.375% Senior Notes due 2024, a principle amount of $143,592,000 with 71.80%. As previously announced, the exchange offer for the 2019 Notes was conditioned upon a minimum of $200,000,000 aggregate principal amount outstanding of 2019 Notes being tendered, and that condition has been satisfied. The exchange offer for the 2024 Notes was not conditioned upon any minimum amount of 2024 Notes being tendered. The consideration for each $1,000 principal amount of old notes validly tendered (and not validly withdrawn) prior to October 4, 2016 (the early tender date) and accepted for exchange pursuant to the exchange offers will be the principal amount of the new secured notes with respect to such series of old notes, plus a cash payment of $53 in the case of the 2019 Notes and $40 in the case of the 2024 Notes. The consideration for each $1,000 principal amount of old notes validly tendered (and not validly withdrawn) after the early tender date, but before the expiration date, and accepted for exchange pursuant to the exchange offers will be the principal amount of the new secured notes with respect to such series of old notes, but without any cash payment. Holders whose old notes are exchanged in the exchange offers will also receive accrued and unpaid interest from the most recent interest payment date for the old notes up to, but not including, the settlement date.


Cloud Peak Energy Units Start Offers to Exchange $400 Million of 2019
Sep 12 16
Cloud Peak Energy Inc. (CLD) announced on September 12, 2016 its direct and indirect wholly-owned subsidiaries, Cloud Peak Energy Resources LLC and Cloud Peak Energy Finance Corp., have commenced offers to exchange their outstanding senior notes for new debt. The new debt consists of secured 12% second lien notes due 2021 to be issued by the two units, according to a statement. The exchange offers are for 8.50% senior notes due 2019 and 6.375% senior notes due 2024. The issuers are offering to exchange up to $400 million aggregate principal amount of old notes. The offer for the 8.50% senior notes is conditioned upon a minimum of $200 million aggregate principal amount outstanding of the 2019 notes being tendered. The offer for 6.375% notes is not conditioned upon any minimum tender amount.


